1) POLICY RULES:
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and is adjacent to a falling token ('F') (seen in ~3/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and is adjacent to a drawn token ('D') (seen in ~2/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there are no red tokens ('R') in the same row to the left (seen in ~4/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there are no red tokens ('R') in the same column above (seen in ~3/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there are static tokens ('S') in the same row below (seen in ~2/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there is an advance token ('A') in the same row (seen in ~2/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there are no drawn tokens ('D') in the same column below (seen in ~3/5 demos).
- Click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there is a static token ('S') in the same column above (seen in ~2/5 demos).

2) COUNTERFACTUAL DISTRACTORS:
- Do not click if the cell (row, col) contains a red token ('R') (seen in ~4/5 demos).
- Do not click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there is a falling token ('F') directly above (seen in ~3/5 demos).
- Do not click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there is a drawn token ('D') directly below (seen in ~2/5 demos).
- Do not click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there are static tokens ('S') in the same row above (seen in ~3/5 demos).
- Do not click if the cell (row, col) is empty ('.') and there are red tokens ('R') in the same column below (seen in ~2/5 demos).

3) GAME DYNAMICS:
- Clicking an empty cell ('.') can lead to the appearance of a drawn token ('D') in the next state (s_t+1).
- Clicking an empty cell ('.') adjacent to a falling token ('F') can lead to the falling token being removed in the next state (s_t+1).
- Clicking an empty cell ('.') can also lead to the appearance of static tokens ('S') in the next state (s_t+1).
- If a drawn token ('D') is clicked, it may lead to the removal of adjacent red tokens ('R') in the next state (s_t+1).
- Clicking an advance token ('A') can lead to the advancement of the game state, potentially changing the layout of tokens in the next state (s_t+1).

4) TOKEN MAP:
TOKEN_MAP = {
